==English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /kraʊʧ/

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[cruc|crūċ]].

====Noun====
'''crouch''' ''(obsolete)''
# a [[cross]]

===Etymology 2===
Perhaps from Old French [[crochir]].

====Intransitive verb====

'''to crouch'''

#To [[bend]] [[down]]; to [[stoop]] [[low]]; to lie close to the ground with legs bent, as an animal when waiting for prey, or in fear.
#To bend [[servile]]ly; to stoop meanly; to [[fawn]]; to [[cringe]].
#To [[sign]] with the [[cross]]; to [[bless]].
#To bend, or cause to bend, as in [[humility]] or [[fear]].

====Noun====
#(countable) a bent or stooped [[position]] 
#:''He waited in a '''crouch''', hidden behind the hedge.''

